1
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:15,400
<i> Dad, take care, okay?</i>

2
00:00:15,533 --> 00:00:17,000
<i> Remember what I told you.</i>

3
00:00:17,133 --> 00:00:19,600
<i>And don't tell your mom
that I'm going to see her,</i>

4
00:00:19,733 --> 00:00:21,700
<i> It'll ruin my surprise.</i>

5
00:00:21,833 --> 00:00:22,833
<i> Cheaters.</i>

6
00:00:22,967 --> 00:00:24,667
<i> Where could they be going?</i>

7
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:26,333
<i> Probably on a honeymoon.</i>

8
00:00:26,467 --> 00:00:27,567
<i> Felma?</i>

9
00:00:27,700 --> 00:00:28,667
<i> Oh my God!</i>

10
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:33,867
<i>Why didn't you tell me
you were already better?</i>

11
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:36,033
<i> I wanted to surprise you.</i>

12
00:00:36,200 --> 00:00:38,833
<i>Felma isn't feeling well,
Manuel.</i>

13
00:00:38,967 --> 00:00:40,233
<i>That's exactly why I want
to bring her with me,</i>

14
00:00:40,367 --> 00:00:41,933
<i> so I can take care of her!</i>

15
00:00:42,067 --> 00:00:44,000
<i> We can't both stay here.</i>

16
00:00:44,133 --> 00:00:44,967
<i> But, Felma!</i>

17
00:00:45,100 --> 00:00:47,400
<i> Enough! Can you just leave?</i>

18
00:00:47,533 --> 00:00:49,133
<i>I have so much
on my mind already,</i>

19
00:00:49,267 --> 00:00:50,467
<i> and you're just adding to it!</i>

20
00:00:50,600 --> 00:00:53,633
<i>Should we tell Dad that Hazel
came back here?</i>

21
00:00:53,767 --> 00:00:54,600
<i> Stop!</i>

22
00:00:54,733 --> 00:00:55,533
<i> Where's Manuel?</i>

23
00:00:55,667 --> 00:00:57,633
<i> Why should I tell you?</i>

24
00:00:57,767 --> 00:01:03,200
<i>- What did you say?
- Let go of my sister!</i>

25
00:01:03,333 --> 00:01:05,667
<i>I shouldn't have spoken
to him like that.</i>

26
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:10,533
<i>Didn't your cousin say I'd
experience behavioral changes?</i>

27
00:01:10,700 --> 00:01:12,467
<i> I'm scared.</i>

28
00:01:15,733 --> 00:01:18,100
Bro, I'm telling you.
Felma is hiding something.

29
00:01:20,867 --> 00:01:24,800
Don't get mad, okay?

30
00:01:24,933 --> 00:01:27,633
Maybe it's just
jealousy talking.

31
00:01:27,767 --> 00:01:30,867
Don't you find her
reaction strange?

32
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:34,200
Kind of. Her eyes suddenly
looked furious.

33
00:01:34,333 --> 00:01:36,567
I only ever saw that
when she was mad at Hazel.

34
00:01:36,700 --> 00:01:38,367
- That's not it.
- Then what?

35
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:42,167
Bro, she chose work
over our kids.

36
00:01:42,333 --> 00:01:43,433
Yeah, now that you mention it.

37
00:01:45,133 --> 00:01:48,933
She knows Hazel's
causing trouble,

38
00:01:49,067 --> 00:01:51,767
yet she still won't come home
to Manila.

39
00:01:51,900 --> 00:01:53,733
Bro, I know Felma.

40
00:01:53,867 --> 00:01:55,200
She'd abandon our business

41
00:01:55,333 --> 00:01:57,433
if it meant keeping our kids
safe from Hazel.

42
00:01:59,633 --> 00:02:03,333
Why didn't you tell
me what Hazel did?

43
00:02:03,467 --> 00:02:05,967
If Joel hadn't called
your Uncle Noah,

44
00:02:06,100 --> 00:02:07,067
I wouldn't have known.

45
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:11,000
We didn't want you
and Dad to worry.

46
00:02:11,133 --> 00:02:14,300
Mom, have you
seen him already?

47
00:02:14,467 --> 00:02:16,200
Yes, dear.

48
00:02:16,333 --> 00:02:21,067
I still can't believe
he can walk again.

49
00:02:21,200 --> 00:02:23,767
It's a beautiful new beginning
for us, Mom, right?

50
00:02:23,900 --> 00:02:25,233
Yes, son.

51
00:02:25,367 --> 00:02:27,267
When are you coming home?

52
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:28,933
Not yet, sweetie.

53
00:02:29,067 --> 00:02:32,067
Your dad will return first.

54
00:02:33,767 --> 00:02:35,367
Why aren't you coming together?

55
00:02:37,700 --> 00:02:40,267
I still have something
to take care of here.

56
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:41,667
Mom

57
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:44,100
So when are you
really coming home?

58
00:02:44,233 --> 00:02:48,100
I'm excited for all of us
to be together again with Dad.

59
00:02:48,267 --> 00:02:49,700
Me, too, sweetie.

60
00:02:49,833 --> 00:02:54,467
Hazel is even more excited
to attack you, Ma'am.

61
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:58,267
Don't worry.

62
00:02:58,400 --> 00:03:00,967
I'll handle her.

63
00:03:01,100 --> 00:03:02,433
That's my Ma'am Felma.

64
00:03:45,900 --> 00:03:47,033
What is this?

65
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:49,900
You took it with wine?

66
00:03:53,267 --> 00:03:55,333
I had a headache.

67
00:03:55,500 --> 00:03:57,300
Do you want to die?

68
00:03:57,433 --> 00:03:59,133
You don't sound like a nurse
at all.

69
00:04:00,267 --> 00:04:03,833
You know painkillers
and alcohol don't mix.

70
00:04:03,967 --> 00:04:05,400
I'm fine.

71
00:04:05,533 --> 00:04:07,800
It was a low dose.

72
00:04:07,933 --> 00:04:10,200
Low dose, sure.
But how many did you take?

73
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:12,633
Let's go to the hospital.
Get checked.

74
00:04:12,767 --> 00:04:13,700
I don't want to.

75
00:04:15,467 --> 00:04:18,600
What are you doing?

76
00:04:18,733 --> 00:04:22,000
I'm checking Abel's page.

77
00:04:23,233 --> 00:04:24,633
I can't find anything.

78
00:04:24,767 --> 00:04:26,467
I don't know where...

79
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:30,700
Manuel and Felma went.
I'm looking here, nothing.

80
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:36,167
Hey!

81
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:37,833
What are you doing?

82
00:04:37,967 --> 00:04:39,200
Why?

83
00:04:40,267 --> 00:04:41,467
Give it to me.

84
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:43,033
Give it back!

85
00:04:43,167 --> 00:04:45,833
Do you want Jessica
to see you like this?

86
00:04:47,900 --> 00:04:50,467
Friend, move on already.

87
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:52,567
Forget Manuel.

88
00:04:54,467 --> 00:04:55,667
And what?

89
00:04:56,733 --> 00:04:58,767
Just let them be happy?

90
00:04:58,900 --> 00:05:00,400
While I'm...

91
00:05:00,533 --> 00:05:01,633
left alone?

92
00:05:03,633 --> 00:05:05,433
So what's your plan?

93
00:05:05,567 --> 00:05:08,600
Get pregnant by someone
else and tell Manuel it's his?

94
00:05:08,733 --> 00:05:09,367
Is that it?

95
00:05:14,533 --> 00:05:17,733
You're crazy. You actually
thought about it, didn't you?

96
00:05:17,867 --> 00:05:19,700
Hey, I was just joking.

97
00:05:19,833 --> 00:05:21,500
Why not?

98
00:05:21,633 --> 00:05:25,200
You know, that's actually
a good idea.

99
00:05:25,333 --> 00:05:32,733
Maybe it's the way to make
Manuel come back to me. Right?

100
00:05:32,867 --> 00:05:34,067
You're good.

101
00:05:41,067 --> 00:05:42,500
No. Wait, I'll get it.

102
00:05:55,900 --> 00:05:57,067
Hazel Cruz?

103
00:05:57,200 --> 00:05:59,233
Yes?

104
00:05:59,367 --> 00:06:00,833
Please receive this, Ma'am.

105
00:06:05,867 --> 00:06:07,967
Thank you.

106
00:06:08,133 --> 00:06:09,133
What is it?

107
00:06:21,167 --> 00:06:24,300
A restraining order.

108
00:06:24,433 --> 00:06:27,800
Felma filed a restraining order
against me.

109
00:06:35,067 --> 00:06:37,233
Atty. Yeban texted me.

110
00:06:38,300 --> 00:06:41,600
The TRO against Hazel
has already been served.

111
00:06:42,667 --> 00:06:44,200
That's good news.

112
00:06:44,333 --> 00:06:47,967
At least you can focus
on getting better.

113
00:06:49,833 --> 00:06:51,667
That is, if I even get better.

114
00:06:52,867 --> 00:06:54,767
Felma, please.

115
00:06:54,900 --> 00:06:56,533
Don't say that.

116
00:06:56,667 --> 00:06:58,400
Emil is a good doctor.

117
00:06:58,533 --> 00:07:01,533
And if there's any treatment or
procedure not available here,

118
00:07:01,667 --> 00:07:03,400
we'll go abroad.

119
00:07:03,533 --> 00:07:06,100
We'll do everything just
for you to get well.

120
00:07:06,233 --> 00:07:08,800
It's hard to hope.

121
00:07:08,933 --> 00:07:11,533
What matters to me now

122
00:07:11,667 --> 00:07:13,333
is making sure...

123
00:07:13,467 --> 00:07:16,500
the kids' lives are in order.

124
00:07:16,667 --> 00:07:19,333
It's a big help that
Manuel is with them now.

125
00:07:22,867 --> 00:07:25,533
Why do you think...

126
00:07:25,667 --> 00:07:27,933
I'd abandon them if you're gone?

127
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:31,367
It's not like that.

128
00:07:32,567 --> 00:07:34,733
Manuel is still different.

129
00:07:34,867 --> 00:07:37,100
He's their father.

130
00:07:37,233 --> 00:07:39,000
Felma, I think of them
as my own children, too.

131
00:07:40,067 --> 00:07:42,167
And I'll do everything for them.

132
00:07:42,300 --> 00:07:44,167
Whatever happens.

133
00:07:44,300 --> 00:07:46,433
Thank you...

134
00:07:46,567 --> 00:07:48,200
for everything.

135
00:07:48,367 --> 00:07:50,933
You've helped us
more than enough.

136
00:07:52,233 --> 00:07:54,033
I'm already ashamed because...

137
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:57,600
because I can't repay you.

138
00:07:57,733 --> 00:07:58,867
Felma,

139
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:01,033
none of this nonsense, okay?

140
00:08:01,167 --> 00:08:02,667
I'm at your service.

141
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:07,433
Always. Now tell me.
What do you need?

142
00:08:07,567 --> 00:08:10,200
I want to talk to Atty. Yeban

143
00:08:10,333 --> 00:08:12,100
about my last will.

144
00:08:14,733 --> 00:08:16,000
Felma, what is it now?

145
00:08:16,133 --> 00:08:18,367
I need to do this

146
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:21,067
so I can have peace of mind.

147
00:08:21,233 --> 00:08:25,167
I wrote everything
down last night.

148
00:08:29,167 --> 00:08:30,133
Okay.

149
00:08:31,967 --> 00:08:34,300
Give it to me.

150
00:08:34,433 --> 00:08:37,033
I'll talk to Atty. Yeban myself.

151
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:44,133
Yes, sorry about that, son.

152
00:08:44,267 --> 00:08:46,667
Your mom's been asking me
to come home since yesterday.

153
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:48,633
But I can't leave her.

154
00:08:48,767 --> 00:08:50,433
It's okay, Dad. You don't need
to worry about us here.

155
00:08:50,567 --> 00:08:54,167
Mom has already filed
a TRO against Hazel.

156
00:08:54,300 --> 00:08:55,767
A restraining order?

157
00:08:55,933 --> 00:08:57,767
Yes. Didn't Mom tell you?

158
00:09:00,667 --> 00:09:03,000
Maybe she just forgot.

159
00:09:04,033 --> 00:09:07,200
Alright, son. I need to go now.
I'll call again.

160
00:09:07,333 --> 00:09:09,100
Okay, Dad. Take care.

161
00:09:10,167 --> 00:09:11,400
Let's go, bro.

162
00:09:16,433 --> 00:09:17,833
Good morning, Sir.

163
00:09:19,233 --> 00:09:20,733
Good morning, Miss.

164
00:09:20,867 --> 00:09:23,500
Which floor
is the conference on?

165
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:25,467
I'm sorry, Sir.

166
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:28,233
There's no conference
scheduled today.

167
00:09:28,400 --> 00:09:30,567
You might be
at the wrong hotel .

168
00:09:37,567 --> 00:09:41,267
<i>We have a business conference to
attend.</i>

169
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:42,767
<i> Tomorrow.</i>

170
00:09:44,300 --> 00:09:45,600
<i> Don't you trust me?</i>

171
00:09:45,733 --> 00:09:47,733
<i> I trust you. Not him.</i>

172
00:09:47,867 --> 00:09:50,533
<i>How many times
do I have to tell you?</i>

173
00:09:50,667 --> 00:09:52,900
<i> He's just helping me!</i>

174
00:10:00,033 --> 00:10:02,200
Felma cheated on me, bro!

175
00:10:02,367 --> 00:10:04,133
Bro, maybe
there's another reason .

176
00:10:04,267 --> 00:10:06,733
Don't think badly
of Felma just yet.

177
00:10:06,867 --> 00:10:09,167
What other reason
could there be?

178
00:10:09,300 --> 00:10:10,367
She and Noah
are having an affair.

179
00:10:10,500 --> 00:10:11,833
She's just hiding it from me.

180
00:10:11,967 --> 00:10:13,833
Why would she do that?

181
00:10:13,967 --> 00:10:16,267
I don't know.
Maybe she wants revenge.

182
00:10:16,400 --> 00:10:19,733
When I married Hazel, I
hid it too, didn't I?

183
00:10:21,100 --> 00:10:22,633
I don't know, bro.

184
00:10:22,767 --> 00:10:24,367
I could be wrong.

185
00:10:24,500 --> 00:10:25,833
But...

186
00:10:25,967 --> 00:10:28,433
I can't stop thinking about it.

187
00:10:51,333 --> 00:10:52,367
Who are you?

188
00:10:55,933 --> 00:10:57,000
Son!

189
00:10:57,133 --> 00:10:58,967
Son!

190
00:10:59,100 --> 00:11:01,367
Where are Didang and the kids?

191
00:11:01,500 --> 00:11:03,267
Where are my children?

192
00:11:05,100 --> 00:11:07,333
Felma, you're in Davao.

193
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:09,300
You're with Noah.

194
00:11:09,433 --> 00:11:10,433
Noah?

195
00:11:10,567 --> 00:11:12,733
- Miss Lucy, what happened?
- Noah.

196
00:11:12,867 --> 00:11:14,967
She doesn't remember
where she is.

197
00:11:15,100 --> 00:11:16,967
She doesn't even recognize me.

198
00:11:17,100 --> 00:11:18,400
Noah.

199
00:11:18,533 --> 00:11:20,300
What's happening to me?

200
00:11:20,433 --> 00:11:21,867
Felma? You're safe here.

201
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:24,933
What's happening to me?

202
00:11:25,067 --> 00:11:28,433
You're here in Davao because
you're undergoing treatment.

203
00:11:28,567 --> 00:11:31,267
<i>This tumor is causing
increased intracranial pressure.</i>

204
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:33,133
<i>Or pressure
inside your skull.</i>

205
00:11:33,267 --> 00:11:36,600
<i>That's why you often have
headaches and feel dizzy.</i>

206
00:11:36,733 --> 00:11:39,833
<i>Your symptoms
may get worse.</i>

207
00:11:39,967 --> 00:11:45,633
<i>Your vision, mobility,
behavior, mood,</i>

208
00:11:45,800 --> 00:11:48,000
<i>and even your personality
could be affected.</i>

209
00:11:49,567 --> 00:11:51,833
Noah...

210
00:11:58,100 --> 00:12:01,267
I'm scared.

211
00:12:10,967 --> 00:12:14,533
Joel, thank you
for picking up Coleen.

212
00:12:14,700 --> 00:12:15,433
- No worries.
- Sorry,

213
00:12:15,567 --> 00:12:17,700
my brother's at the factory.

214
00:12:17,833 --> 00:12:20,033
It's okay. I'm happy to do that.

215
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:24,333
Sis, have you talked to Dad?

216
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:27,667
Not yet.

217
00:12:29,733 --> 00:12:31,167
Is something wrong?

218
00:12:32,133 --> 00:12:35,767
Because Mom and Dad's talk
didn't seem to go well.

219
00:12:35,900 --> 00:12:38,167
She made Dad come
back here right away.

220
00:12:38,300 --> 00:12:42,200
And Dad didn't even
know about the TRO.

221
00:12:42,333 --> 00:12:43,767
Let go of me! Let go!
Let go of me!

222
00:12:43,900 --> 00:12:45,133
I don't care! Hey!

223
00:12:45,267 --> 00:12:46,400
You three, what is this?

224
00:12:46,533 --> 00:12:48,167
- Ma'am.
- Let go of me!

225
00:12:48,333 --> 00:12:49,833
- Let go of me!
- Ma'am!

226
00:12:49,967 --> 00:12:51,267
What is this, huh?

227
00:12:51,400 --> 00:12:53,100
What is this?

228
00:12:53,233 --> 00:12:56,467
You don't know what a TRO means?

229
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:58,400
TRO, TRO whatever!

230
00:12:58,533 --> 00:13:00,767
I don't care about
your mother's little tricks!

231
00:13:01,900 --> 00:13:03,233
You know,

232
00:13:03,367 --> 00:13:06,300
you could go to jail
for violating that.

233
00:13:06,433 --> 00:13:07,567
Really?

234
00:13:07,700 --> 00:13:09,533
It's so rich coming from you.

235
00:13:09,667 --> 00:13:11,500
You know...

236
00:13:11,633 --> 00:13:13,533
you're the one
who should have this.

237
00:13:13,667 --> 00:13:15,333
My child died
because of you.

238
00:13:15,467 --> 00:13:18,800
If you had a restraining order,
Jessica wouldn't have died.

239
00:13:20,167 --> 00:13:21,333
So here you go!

240
00:13:22,933 --> 00:13:24,800
- Eat it!
- Wait.

241
00:13:24,933 --> 00:13:26,767
- Eat it! Eat it!
- Hazel.

242
00:13:39,133 --> 00:13:40,867
- Get out of here! No!
- Let's go, Ma'am!

243
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:43,700
Tell your mom and dad
when they get back!

244
00:13:43,833 --> 00:13:45,267
Hey! Let go of me!

245
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:47,600
Why are you dragging me away?

246
00:13:55,733 --> 00:13:56,667
Hello, Coleen?

247
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:59,300
Uncle Noah, is Mom with you?

248
00:13:59,433 --> 00:14:01,867
Yes, but...

249
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:03,433
she's resting now.

250
00:14:03,567 --> 00:14:05,967
Uncle, Hazel attacked us.

251
00:14:06,100 --> 00:14:08,467
She's being taken
to the police station.

252
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:09,600
What?

253
00:14:09,733 --> 00:14:10,667
Yes.

254
00:14:10,800 --> 00:14:13,900
But Uncle, we don't know
what's happening to Mom.

255
00:14:14,033 --> 00:14:16,467
We can't even reach Dad.

256
00:14:16,600 --> 00:14:18,800
We need them here now.

257
00:14:19,767 --> 00:14:20,900
Felma!

258
00:14:22,367 --> 00:14:24,567
Felma, come out! Let's talk!

259
00:14:24,700 --> 00:14:27,200
Dear, I'll call you back.

260
00:14:27,333 --> 00:14:28,133
Bye.

261
00:14:28,300 --> 00:14:29,267
I'm going back there!

262
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:30,133
No!

263
00:14:42,767 --> 00:14:44,167
What?

264
00:14:51,667 --> 00:14:53,000
Hazel?

265
00:14:53,133 --> 00:14:54,867
Hazel?

266
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:56,600
- Felma!
- Wait!

267
00:14:57,800 --> 00:14:59,500
What is it, Manuel?

268
00:14:59,633 --> 00:15:00,933
Where's Felma?

269
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:02,267
She's resting.

270
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:04,100
You know
she's not feeling well.

271
00:15:04,233 --> 00:15:06,433
You're such a liar.

272
00:15:06,567 --> 00:15:09,667
You know what, Manuel?
Coleen just called me.

273
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:11,967
Hazel attacked them.

274
00:15:12,100 --> 00:15:14,467
The police are taking her in.

275
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:15,467
What?

276
00:15:15,600 --> 00:15:17,700
- Bro, let's go home.
- No, wait. Felma!

277
00:15:17,833 --> 00:15:19,433
- Manuel, please!
- Felma, let's talk!

278
00:15:19,567 --> 00:15:21,500
- Stop making a scene!
- Just a minute!

279
00:15:21,633 --> 00:15:23,867
- Felma!
- Go to your kids!

280
00:15:26,067 --> 00:15:27,933
You're such a liar!

281
00:15:28,067 --> 00:15:29,733
I know you and Felma
are hiding something.

282
00:15:29,867 --> 00:15:33,933
I went to the hotel.
There was no conference!

283
00:15:34,067 --> 00:15:36,167
I know you're both fooling me!

284
00:15:36,333 --> 00:15:38,000
What are you really doing here
with Felma?

285
00:15:38,133 --> 00:15:40,100
Don't point at me!

286
00:15:40,233 --> 00:15:41,567
Bro! Bro!

287
00:15:41,700 --> 00:15:42,800
That's enough!

288
00:15:42,933 --> 00:15:45,733
Stop it. Noah, Noah, please.

289
00:15:45,867 --> 00:15:48,333
- Bro, don't.
- Take your friend home.

290
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:51,733
Don't make a scene here.

291
00:15:53,367 --> 00:15:55,067
Noah!

292
00:15:55,200 --> 00:15:56,600
Felma!

293
00:15:58,367 --> 00:15:59,333
Felma!

294
00:16:04,367 --> 00:16:05,467
Felma!

295
00:16:08,367 --> 00:16:09,433
What's happening?

296
00:16:10,967 --> 00:16:13,467
She's just acting.
Mister, please pick her up.

297
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:14,700
Take her outside.

298
00:16:17,633 --> 00:16:18,867
Sis?

299
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:20,400
Sis, she's not breathing.

300
00:16:21,700 --> 00:16:23,033
Hazel?

301
00:16:23,167 --> 00:16:24,400
- Hazel!
- Hazel?

302
00:16:25,800 --> 00:16:26,467
Hazel?

303
00:16:26,600 --> 00:16:29,900
Noah! Noah! Noah, it's Felma!

304
00:16:30,033 --> 00:16:32,133
Help! Noah!

305
00:16:32,267 --> 00:16:35,300
- Noah, it's Felma!
- Felma! Felma!

306
00:16:35,433 --> 00:16:36,867
- I don't know what to do.
- Felma!

307
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:39,633
- Felma!
- Let's call an ambulance!

308
00:16:39,767 --> 00:16:41,500
- What's happening to her?
- Felma!

309
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:44,333
No, we can't touch her.

310
00:16:44,467 --> 00:16:45,767
Felma!

311
00:16:45,900 --> 00:16:47,567
- Felma!
- Let's call an ambulance!

312
00:16:47,700 --> 00:16:48,967
Felma!

313
00:17:00,933 --> 00:17:02,333
Are you sure
it wasn't intentional?

314
00:17:02,467 --> 00:17:03,967
She might just be trying
to get sympathy.

315
00:17:04,100 --> 00:17:05,167
Knowing her?

316
00:17:05,300 --> 00:17:06,067
It's possible.

317
00:17:08,667 --> 00:17:11,033
Are you Hazel Cruz's family?

318
00:17:11,167 --> 00:17:12,367
No.

319
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:15,233
But we're the ones
who brought her here.

320
00:17:15,400 --> 00:17:17,533
I need to speak
to a family member.

321
00:17:17,667 --> 00:17:21,667
Is her husband or child here?

322
00:17:21,800 --> 00:17:23,433
She and her husband
are separated.

323
00:17:26,033 --> 00:17:27,267
Her child has passed away.

324
00:17:28,567 --> 00:17:30,733
Only Satan is left
as her relative.

325
00:17:30,867 --> 00:17:31,967
- Andrea.
- Sis.

326
00:17:33,967 --> 00:17:35,067
Well...

327
00:17:36,600 --> 00:17:37,800
we're her stepchildren.

328
00:17:39,700 --> 00:17:41,567
Our father hasn't arrived yet.

329
00:17:41,700 --> 00:17:43,433
I see.

330
00:17:43,567 --> 00:17:45,633
How is she, Doctor?

331
00:17:45,767 --> 00:17:50,433
We found a mix of alcohol
and painkillers in her system.

332
00:17:50,600 --> 00:17:51,700
It's not a lethal dose,

333
00:17:51,833 --> 00:17:55,233
but it's enough
to cause respiratory depression.

334
00:17:55,367 --> 00:17:57,467
A slowing of her breathing.

335
00:17:58,667 --> 00:18:02,100
But Doctor, she's a nurse.
She should've known better.

336
00:18:02,233 --> 00:18:05,033
Is it possible
that she's suicidal?

337
00:18:11,333 --> 00:18:13,467
Doctor, what happened to Felma?

338
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:16,833
We need to run tests before we
can say for sure.

339
00:18:16,967 --> 00:18:18,100
Are you her husband?

340
00:18:23,667 --> 00:18:25,733
Yes, Doctor

341
00:18:25,867 --> 00:18:27,833
Does she have any history
of seizures?

342
00:18:27,967 --> 00:18:29,767
No, Doctor.

343
00:18:29,900 --> 00:18:32,733
Any history of stroke or...

344
00:18:32,867 --> 00:18:34,767
None.

345
00:18:34,900 --> 00:18:36,267
How about cancer?

346
00:18:36,400 --> 00:18:37,700
None.

347
00:18:40,633 --> 00:18:41,833
She has.

348
00:18:42,900 --> 00:18:43,900
What?

349
00:18:48,267 --> 00:18:49,600
Frontal lobe...

350
00:18:51,467 --> 00:18:52,433
meningioma.

351
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:56,100
Who's her oncologist?

352
00:18:59,033 --> 00:19:00,033
Neuro.

353
00:19:01,733 --> 00:19:03,933
Dr. Emil Yunque.

354
00:19:04,067 --> 00:19:05,467
I need to speak with him.

355
00:19:06,967 --> 00:19:09,533
I've already contacted him.
He's on his way.

356
00:19:11,633 --> 00:19:12,900
Excuse me.

357
00:19:19,933 --> 00:19:21,200
Why didn't you
tell me right away?

358
00:19:21,333 --> 00:19:23,067
Or at least tell the kids?

359
00:19:24,833 --> 00:19:27,533
We have the right to know
what's happening to Felma.

360
00:19:31,033 --> 00:19:32,800
Felma didn't want
to tell you.

361
00:19:33,333 --> 00:19:36,100
She didn't want to add
to your problems.

362
00:19:52,600 --> 00:19:56,500
Felma, why didn't you tell me
about your condition right away?

363
00:19:58,667 --> 00:20:00,400
I didn't want you to worry.

364
00:20:05,133 --> 00:20:07,600
That's why I lied...

365
00:20:07,733 --> 00:20:09,467
to the kids.

366
00:20:11,367 --> 00:20:13,533
I told them that...

367
00:20:15,367 --> 00:20:17,167
I just needed to rest.

368
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:20,000
That's why I
went on vacation.

369
00:20:22,400 --> 00:20:24,300
I'm really useless.

370
00:20:28,467 --> 00:20:30,333
No, Felma.

371
00:20:30,467 --> 00:20:32,533
Look at you.
You're the one who's sick,

372
00:20:32,667 --> 00:20:34,967
yet you're still thinking
about us.

373
00:20:36,633 --> 00:20:37,967
While I let...

374
00:20:39,467 --> 00:20:42,467
my jealousy take over.

375
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:44,800
I even said things
I shouldn't have.

376
00:20:47,767 --> 00:20:49,133
It's my fault, too.

377
00:20:50,400 --> 00:20:51,833
Because...

378
00:20:53,467 --> 00:20:56,200
if you had known the truth,

379
00:20:57,800 --> 00:21:00,800
you wouldn't have doubted
Noah and me.

380
00:21:03,467 --> 00:21:04,933
I'm sorry.

381
00:21:07,333 --> 00:21:08,500
Felma...

382
00:21:11,467 --> 00:21:13,667
we'll fight this together, okay?

383
00:21:14,967 --> 00:21:17,600
And have faith
that you'll get better.

384
00:21:17,733 --> 00:21:19,900
You'll get better, Felma. Okay?

385
00:21:25,167 --> 00:21:26,833
Doctor.

386
00:21:26,967 --> 00:21:29,800
Noah has already discussed
the symptoms

387
00:21:29,933 --> 00:21:31,667
you've had these past few days.

388
00:21:31,800 --> 00:21:33,200
Doctor...

389
00:21:33,333 --> 00:21:34,533
what can we do?

390
00:21:34,667 --> 00:21:37,167
Anything, just so Felma
can recover.

391
00:21:37,300 --> 00:21:41,433
Because your tumor is aggressive
and symptomatic,

392
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:44,300
I strongly suggest surgery
as soon as possible.

393
00:21:46,533 --> 00:21:47,833
Felma,

394
00:21:47,967 --> 00:21:49,300
I think you should do it.

395
00:21:50,300 --> 00:21:51,667
That's your best chance.

396
00:21:52,700 --> 00:21:54,433
I read online...

397
00:21:56,333 --> 00:21:59,867
that there are
non-surgical options.

398
00:22:01,400 --> 00:22:05,533
Yes, but surgery
is still the best option.

399
00:22:05,667 --> 00:22:08,367
We can try chemo and radiation.

400
00:22:08,500 --> 00:22:10,733
There's no
guarantee, of course.

401
00:22:10,867 --> 00:22:14,867
But if they work,
the tumor may shrink.

402
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:17,100
Doctor, what if...

403
00:22:17,267 --> 00:22:18,133
what if it doesn't?

404
00:22:18,267 --> 00:22:20,833
The risk is that by then,

405
00:22:20,967 --> 00:22:23,367
it might be too late
for surgery.

406
00:22:23,500 --> 00:22:26,033
And we'll have no other way
to save your life.

407
00:22:26,167 --> 00:22:27,233
I'm sorry.

408
00:22:29,300 --> 00:22:31,000
Doc...

409
00:22:31,133 --> 00:22:32,967
Felma will undergo surgery.
Right, Felma?

410
00:22:33,100 --> 00:22:34,967
No.

411
00:22:35,100 --> 00:22:37,467
I don't want surgery.

412
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:38,933
I don't want it.

413
00:22:52,833 --> 00:22:54,900
- Nurse! Take this off.
- I'm sorry.

414
00:22:55,033 --> 00:22:56,733
We're just following
the doctor's orders.

415
00:22:56,867 --> 00:22:57,700
Doctor's orders?

416
00:22:57,833 --> 00:22:58,800
Or their orders?

417
00:22:58,933 --> 00:23:00,933
You should've just left me!

418
00:23:01,067 --> 00:23:02,833
So I could already be
with Jessica.

419
00:23:02,967 --> 00:23:04,167
Have her arrested.

420
00:23:04,300 --> 00:23:05,000
Okay.

421
00:23:05,133 --> 00:23:06,200
Dad, when are you coming back?

422
00:23:06,333 --> 00:23:08,033
That depends on your mom.

423
00:23:08,167 --> 00:23:09,400
Probably a few more days.

424
00:23:09,533 --> 00:23:12,133
Alice, help me get out of here.

425
00:23:12,267 --> 00:23:15,200
Do you want to add
fugitive to your list of crimes?

426
00:23:15,333 --> 00:23:16,333
What are you doing here?

427
00:23:16,467 --> 00:23:17,933
You violated the TRO.

428
00:23:18,067 --> 00:23:19,333
You could go to jail.

429
00:23:19,467 --> 00:23:22,000
We can't hide this
from the kids forever.

430
00:23:22,167 --> 00:23:23,200
Let's go home.

431
00:23:23,333 --> 00:23:24,133
I'm just going to the restroom.

432
00:23:24,267 --> 00:23:25,500
Did Felma come here?

433
00:23:25,633 --> 00:23:26,933
Weren't you with Felma?

434
00:23:27,067 --> 00:23:28,533
I waited outside
the restroom for so long.

435
00:23:28,667 --> 00:23:30,000
Then I had it checked,

436
00:23:30,133 --> 00:23:31,500
and she was gone.
